[5.374325, "o", "---\r\ntype: jira\r\ninstance: https://rustworks.atlassian.net\r\nkey: KAN-10\r\nsummary: OAuth callback fails for users with legacy session cookies\r\nstatus: To Do\r\nissue_type: Bug\r\npriority: Medium\r\nlabels:\r\n- auth\r\n- production\r\n- regression\r\n---\r\n\r\nAfter the auth-provider migration on :date[2025-05-18]{timestamp=1747526400000} a cohort of users see the OAuth callback silently fail. Triage status: :status[In Triage]{color=yellow}.\r\n\r\n:::panel{type=warning}\r\n**Impact**: ~1,200 users locked out of `/dashboard`. Workaround: clear cookies and re-authenticate.\r\n:::\r\n\r\n## Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Sign in via the *legacy* path so the browser holds:\r\n  - A `omni_session=<jwt>` cookie\r\n  - The cookie must **not** carry `SameSite=Lax`\r\n2. Trigger the OAuth flow against the new provider\r\n3. Observe: callback returns `200`, but `/dashboard` redirects back to `/login`\r\n\r\n## Investigation checklist\r\n\r\n"]
[5.376842, "o", "\r\n"]
[6.876842, "x", "0"]
